{
  "text": "Several studies suggested that cardiac biomarkers may be useful for the identification of patients at high risk of developing cardiotoxicity. The most robust results were obtained using cardiac troponin I (cTnI) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] , whereas the role of natriuretic peptides remains less clear [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] [CITATION_12] .",
